<h1>Credits</h1>
<h2>Game Engine</h2>
<p>The KBC game engine is built in Ruby on Rails by Chris Schumann, with help from Claude Code.</p>
<p>Chris is a software engineer based in the Twin Cities, Minnesota area. He has a passion for board games and game design, and built KBC to scratch his own itch for a better digital version of the game.</p>
<h3>Chris's LinkedIn Profile: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chrisschumann/">https://www.linkedin.com/in/chrisschumann/</a></h3>
<h3>Chris's GitHub Profile: <a href="https://github.com/torgoton">https://github.com/torgoton</a></h3>
<h3>The repository for this application: <a href="https://github.com/torgoton/kbc">https://github.com/torgoton/kbc</a></h3>
<p>Claude is a software engineer based in the San Francisco Bay Area. He has a passion for board games and game design, and contributed to KBC by helping to build out the backend API and implementing the game logic.</p>
<p>(Claude wrote both of those bios.)</p>
<h3>Learn more about Claude: <a href="https://claude.com/product/claude-code">https://claude.com/product/claude-code</a></h3>

